nnauj]] fought between Humayun and Sher Shah Suri and Humayun was completely defeated. Humayun lost the Mughal empire to Afghans (Suri Dynasty), and passed 12 years in exile. |- | || Birth of Maharana Pratap Singh of Mewar ( son of Maharana Udai Singh II ) |- | [[1545 in India|1545]] || 22 May || Death of [[Sher Shah Suri]] and succeeded by [[Islam Shah Suri]]. |- | [[1552 in India|1552]] ||26 March || [[Guru Amar Das]] becomes third Guru of Sikhs. |- | [[1554 in India|1554]] || 22 November || Death of [[Islam Shah Suri]]. |- | [[1555 in India|1555]] || || Humayun regained the throne of Delhi from the hands of weak successors of Sher Shah. |- | rowspan="2" style="vertical-align:top;"| [[1556 in India|1556]] || || Humayun converts from [[Sunni Islam]] to [[Shia]] Islam, to gain the alliance of the Shah of [[Persia]]. Humayun dies, and is succeeded by his son [[Akbar]]. |- | || Hindu king [[Hemu]] establishes 'Hindu Raj' in North India and bestowed with title of "Vikramaditya"; [[Battle of Panipat (1556)|Second Battle of Panipat]] fought between Hemu and [[Akbar]]'s forces in which Hemu is killed. |- | [[1565 in India|1565]] || 26 January || [[Battle of Talikota]] results in the rout of Vijayanagara empire. |- | [[1572 in India|1572]] || || Akbar annexes [[Gujarat]], also shifts the Mughal capital to Fatehpur Sikri where a new township and citadel containing buildings of a unique all-India character—inspired by the architecture of Bengal, Gujarat, Malwa, Kashmir as well as the Timurid world—is born. |- | rowspan="2" style="vertical-align:top;"| [[1574 in India|1574]] ||1 September || [[Guru Ram Das]] becomes fourth Guru of Sikhs. |- | || Akbar annexes [[Bengal]]. |- | [[1581 in India|1581]] ||1 September || [[Guru Arjan Dev]] becomes fifth Guru of Sikhs. |- | [[1586 in India|1586]] || || Akbar annexes [[Kashmir]]. |- [[1592 in India Maharana pratap died]] | [[1600 in India|1600]] || 31 December ||East India company is formed in England. Gets exclusive trading rights w