bedkar]] converted to [[Buddhism]] along with 600,000 followers. |- | 6 December || [[B. R. Ambedkar]] passed away. |- | rowspan="2" style="vertical-align:top;" | [[1962 in India|1962]] || || War over disputed territory of Kashmir<ref name="bbc" /> with China. |- | || [[India]] seizes [[Diu, India|Diu]], [[Daman District, India|Daman]] and [[Goa]] from [[Portuguese India]]. |- | [[1964 in India|1964]] || 27 May || Death of Prime Minister [[Jawaharlal Nehru]]. |- | [[1965 in India|1965]] || 6–23 September || [[Indo-Pakistani War of 1965|Second war]] with Pakistan over Kashmir. |- | [[1966 in India|1966]] || || Nehru's daughter [[Indira Gandhi]] becomes prime minister. |- | rowspan="2" style="vertical-align:top;" | [[1971 in India|1971]] || || [[Indo-Pakistani War of 1971|Third war]] with [[Pakistan]] over creation of [[Bangladesh]], formerly East Pakistan. |- | || Twenty-year treaty of friendship signed with Soviet Union. |- | [[1974 in India|1974]] || || [[India]] [[Smiling Buddha|explodes]] first [[nuclear device]] in underground test. |- | rowspan="2" style="vertical-align:top;" | [[1975 in India|1975]] || || [[Indira Gandhi]] declares a state of emergency after being found guilty of electoral malpractice. |- | || Nearly 1,000 political opponents imprisoned and programme of compulsory birth control introduced. (to 1977) |- | [[1977 in India|1977]] || || [[Indira Gandhi]]'s Congress Party loses general elections. Janata Party comes to power. The [[Communist party of India]] comes into power in West Bengal. |- | [[1979 in India|1979]] || || The Janata Party splits. Chaudhary Charan Singh becomes Prime Minister. |- | [[1980 in India|1980]] || || [[Indira Gandhi]] returns to power heading the Congress party splinter group, Congress (Indira). |- | [[1983 in India|1983]] || || [[N. T. Rama Rao]] NTR's nine-month-old Telugu Desam assumes power in AP becoming a challenger post Loknayak Jayprakash Narayan against Indira Gandhi. |- | [[1983 in India|1983]] || || India won 1